subSubSection.paragraph:
Urosternite I (
Figs 202, 203
) with comb of eight macrochaetae and one setula medially on slightly protruding region, urosternite II with 1+1 lateral combs each of eight macrochaetae (right comb missing on deformed part of posterior margin in 
holotype
) and two marginal setulae, urosternites III–VIII (juvenile 
♀
with combs of 2–3 macrochaetae on coxites VIII) with 1+1 lateral combs of four to twelve macrochaetae associated with a cilium at the laterad end and two to five setulae mostly located on the margin or between the comb and the margin but occasionally between the insertion points of the macrochaetae (
Figs 204, 205
). The distance between the lateral combs 1.5–2.1 times the width of these combs. The spacing between the macrochaetae of the combs is always quite wide.
